# Agile Project Execution Document

## Project Title
**Java Batch Final Project – Milestone Four**

## Project Duration
**15 January 2026 – 28 January 2026**

## Development Methodology
**Agile Methodology**  
(Iterative and Incremental Development Approach)

## Technology Stack
- Java  
- Maven  
- Eclipse IDE, IntelliJ IDEA  
- Git & GitHub  

---

## Sprint 1 – Requirement Analysis & Planning
**Date:** 15 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Analyzed the milestone problem statement in detail  
- Understood functional and non-functional requirements  
- Identified project modules and overall structure  
- Finalized development tools and technologies  

### Outcome
- Clear understanding of project scope, requirements, and execution strategy  

---

## Sprint 2 – Project Setup & Environment Configuration
**Date:** 16 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Created Maven-based project structure  
- Configured `pom.xml` with required dependencies  
- Set up source and test directories  
- Initialized Git repository for version control  

### Outcome
- Project environment and base structure successfully prepared  

---

## Sprint 3 – Core Application Development
**Date:** 18 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Implemented core Java classes  
- Developed business logic and workflows  
- Created the main execution flow of the application  
- Followed modular and clean coding practices  

### Outcome
- Core application functionality implemented successfully  

---

## Sprint 4 – Testing & Validation
**Date:** 21 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Created test classes under `src/test/java`  
- Performed unit testing to validate functionality  
- Identified and fixed logical and runtime errors  
- Improved code quality and performance  

### Outcome
- Application tested, validated, and stabilized  

---

## Sprint 5 – Version Control & Repository Management
**Date:** 24 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Cleaned and organized Git commit history  
- Created a new GitHub repository  
- Pushed project with meaningful commits  
- Maintained a clean and structured repository layout  

### Outcome
- Project successfully version-controlled and hosted on GitHub  

---

## Sprint 6 – Documentation & Licensing
**Date:** 27 January 2026

### Activities Performed
- Created a detailed README file  
- Added MIT License to the project  
- Prepared Agile project execution documentation  
- Performed final code review  

### Outcome
- Project fully documented and ready for final submission  

---

## Final Project Status
**Date:** 28 January 2026

- All milestone requirements successfully completed  
- Project developed following Agile methodology  
- Source code and documentation uploaded to GitHub  

---

## Conclusion
This project was developed using the Agile methodology, enabling iterative development, continuous testing, and timely delivery. The structured sprint-wise approach ensured quality implementation, proper documentation, and successful completion of the milestone.
